To set up and run Awoochi locally:

1. $ git pull git@github.com:drusepth/Awoochi.git
2. $ rake db:migrate
3. $ script/server
4. Navigate to http://localhost:3000/

If you're a Ruby/Rails developer, most of the code you'll be working with will
be in app/controllers, app/models, and app/views.

If you're a designer, you'll probably be working in public/stylesheets, 
/public/javascripts, and /app/views.

If you're developing libraries in other languages, you'll probably want to make
a directory in /libraries.

If you're developing plugins for sites like Wordpress, you'll probably want to
make a directory in /plugins.
